mgeiger-datadriver

Inspired/taken from Marook's https://github.com/marook/db-fitnesse.

Added Calendar Date data fixture to fetch dates in the past or dates in the future based on the current Calendar date.
Transitioned original db-fitnesse package from FIT to SLIM.

Examples of Date Data Fixture and Database Query Fixture usage in Xebium test:

|import|
|com.mgeiger.datadriver|

---------------------------------------------
# Date Data Fixture
---------------------------------------------

|Date Data Fixture                                                |
|increment day|echo date?  |echo month?  |echo day?  |echo year?  |
|-30          |$DATESTRING=|$MONTHSTRING=|$DAYSTRING=|$YEARSTRING=|

|Date Data Fixture        |
|minute divisible by five?|
|$MINUTESTRING=           |

!|scenario|Check date fixture                      |
|check    |verify is divisible by five|PASS        |
|check    |echo month                 |$MONTHSTRING|
|check    |echo day                   |$DAYSTRING  |
|check    |echo year                  |$YEARSTRING |

![ script
 Check date fixture
]!

---------------------------------------------
# Query Runner Fixture
---------------------------------------------

|DB Connection                                                                                              |
|db driver                      |db connect                             |user       |password  |get connect?|
|oracle.jdbc.driver.OracleDriver|jdbc:oracle:thin:@<DB_URL>:<PORT>:<SID>|<USER_NAME>|<PASSWORD>|true        |

|Query Runner Fixture                                                   |
|sql                                        |column  |run query get int?|
|SELECT INT FROM TABLE WHERE WHERE INT = INT|<COLUMN>|$INT_OUTPUT=      |


|Query Runner Fixture                                                         |
|sql                                           |column  |run query get string?|
|SELECT STRING FROM TABLE WHERE STRING = STRING|<COLUMN>|$STRING_OUTPUT=      |

Installation:

1. git clone git://github.com/xebia/Xebium

2. git clone git://github.com/msgeiger/mgeiger-datadriver.git

3. cd <into mgeiger-datadriver dir>

4. From the command line run mvn clean install

5. run mvn package

6. Copy the mgeiger-datadriver/src/main/java/com/geiger directory to the Xebium/src/main/java/com directory, or,
   add dependency to Xebium/pom.xml.

    <dependency>
      <groupId>com.mgeiger.datadriver</groupId>
      <artifactId>mgeiger-datadriver</artifactId>
      <version>1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>
      <scope>runtime</scope>
    </dependency>

7. Add oracle jdbc dependency to the Xebium package and Xebium/pom.xml file

    <dependency>
      <groupId>com.oracle</groupId>
      <artifactId>ojdbc6</artifactId>
      <version>11.2.0</version>
      <scope>system</scope>
      <systemPath>${<path to oracle jdbc dir>}/ojdbc6.jar</systemPath>
    </dependency>

8. cd into Xebium

9. run maven clean install

10. run mvn -Pfitnesse test